The paper presents an approach for object detection and categorization using event cameras, which involves computer vision and robotics (cs.CV, cs.RO). The focus on energy efficiency and hardware implementation suggests a potential fit for neural networks and optimization (cs.NE), while the proposed feature extraction and matching methods involve machine learning techniques such as PCA and k-d trees, indicating relevance to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
